OL,3,CWidower says he would 'swap money for
OL,4,Cwife back' after #1 million settlement
OL,6,FSouth Warwickshire NHS Foundation
OL,7,FTrust admitted that the failure to
OL,8,Frefer Rose to cardiology and to place
OL,9,Fher on constant heart monitoring
OL,10,Fconstituted a breach of duty.
OL,12,FThey conceded that had these actions
OL,13,Fbeen taken, she would have been
OL,14,Fcorrectly diagnosed and treated with
OL,15,Fbeta-blocker medication. Even if she
OL,16,Fhad still suffered a cardiac arrest,
OL,17,Fshe would have received immediate
OL,18,Fdefibrillation and resuscitation,
OL,19,Fwhich would have likely saved her life.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G6/10
