OL,6,FRose's husband, left to raise their
OL,7,Fthree children aged 14, nine, and six
OL,8,Fat the time of her death, described
OL,9,Fthe period following his wife's death
OL,10,Fas extremely traumatic.
OL,12,FHe emphasised his desire for justice
OL,13,Ffor his late wife, who had been the
OL,14,Fprimary earner for the family,
OL,15,Fsupporting not only them but also her
OL,16,Fparents and sister in the Philippines.
OL,18,F"As a nurse herself she was really
OL,19,Fcommitted to helping others and she
OL,20,Fhelped to save many lives.
