OL,6,FElizabeth Maliakal, a medical
OL,7,Fnegligence solicitor says: "It's a
OL,8,Freally tragic and heartbreaking case
OL,9,Fof a completely avoidable and totally
OL,10,Funnecessary death. There were several
OL,11,Ffailures throughout the various
OL,12,Fcontacts Rose had with the healthcare
OL,13,Fproviders from the paramedics through
OL,14,Fto the hospital.
OL,16,F"There was a failure on behalf of both
OL,17,Fthe ambulance staff and the hospital
OL,18,Fto find out the correct diagnosis and
OL,19,Fhad they, Rose would be with her
OL,20,Ffamily today."
